    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>A branch of archaeology that reconstructs prehistoric interactions of human or animal populations and their environment through pollen samples, skeletal and seed remains, soil analysis and other such techniques.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
